  "text": "Kafka's log compaction architecture is implemented in the apache/kafka repository (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489). The implementation consists of three main components:\n\n**1. Cleaner Thread (LogCleaner.java):**\nThe LogCleaner class is the main orchestrator for log cleaning. It implements BrokerReconfigurable and manages a pool of CleanerThread instances. Each CleanerThread (nested class extending ShutdownableThread) runs in the background, selecting the dirtiest log partitions with compact cleanup policy and performing cleaning operations. The LogCleaner class is located at storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogCleaner.java and contains the CleanerThread nested class.\n\n**2. Segment Selection Policy (LogCleanerManager.java):**\nThe segment selection policy is implemented in LogCleanerManager (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogCleanerManager.java). The key methods are:\n- grabFilthiestCompactedLog(): Selects the dirtiest log for cleaning based on the cleanable ratio (dirty bytes / total bytes)\n- cleanableOffsets(): Determines which offsets in a log can be cleaned, respecting compaction lag constraints (minCleanableRatio, compactionLagMs, maxCompactionLagMs)\nThe class also manages OffsetsToClean records and PreCleanStats for tracking cleaning progress.\n\n**3. Key-Based Deduplication Logic (Cleaner.java):**\nThe core deduplication logic is in the Cleaner class (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/Cleaner.java). The key methods are:\n- buildOffsetMap(): Creates a key=>offset mapping (OffsetMap) for all messages in the dirty section. This is the foundation for deduplication.\n- buildOffsetMapForSegment(): Builds the offset map segment by segment, using SkimpyOffsetMap as the implementation.\n- shouldRetainRecord(): The critical deduplication decision method. For each message, it checks:\n  * If the message's offset is newer than the latest offset for that key in the map, retain it\n  * If the message has a value, retain it\n  * If the message is a tombstone (null value), check if it's past the delete horizon before discarding\n- cleanInto(): Performs the actual cleaning of segments using a RecordFilter that applies the shouldRetainRecord logic\n- cleanSegments(): Orchestrates cleaning of multiple segments, handling transaction metadata and producer state preservation\n\nSupporting classes include:\n- OffsetMap/SkimpyOffsetMap: Hash-based key=>offset deduplication maps\n- LogToClean: Represents a partition eligible for cleaning with metrics\n- CleanedTransactionMetadata: Tracks aborted transactions and control batch state during cleaning\n- LogConfig: Contains compaction configuration like deleteRetentionMs, minCleanableRatio, compactionLagMs\n- UnifiedLog: The main log structure with methods like lastRecordsOfActiveProducers() used to preserve producer state\n\nThe compaction workflow: LogCleaner schedules CleanerThreads → select log via grabFilthiestCompactedLog() → build OffsetMap via buildOffsetMap() → clean segments via cleanSegments() → filter messages via cleanInto()/shouldRetainRecord() → preserve only latest versions of keys."
